You are continuing MathBoard — a pencil-first, OFFLINE PWA whiteboard for teaching
A-level Mathematics (Cambridge 9709) on iPad + Mac. Author: Waseem Akhlaque.

HARD RULES (never break, no exceptions):
- Vanilla only: plain JavaScript (ES modules) + HTML5 Canvas 2D + CSS. NO framework,
  NO build step, NO TypeScript, NO bundler, NO npm runtime dependencies. It must stay a
  static site runnable with `python3 -m http.server`.
- No backend. Persistence is IndexedDB only (js/storage.js). Must work fully offline.
- All third-party libraries are vendored locally in vendor/. NEVER add a CDN <script>.
  To add a lib, download the file into vendor/ and reference the local path.
- Match the existing code style in js/app.js: small helper functions, terse "why" comments,
  const-first. Read the neighbouring code before adding to any section.
- Wrap EVERY data mutation in beginAction()/commitAction() so undo/redo keeps working.
- CACHE-BUMP RULE: after ANY edit to css/app.css or js/app.js you MUST increment ?v=N on
  BOTH the app.css and app.js tags in index.html, AND bump CACHE='mathboard-vN' in sw.js.
  Forgetting this serves stale code. Do it as the final step of every change.

KEY FILES:
- index.html — single page, both views (library + editor) + all floating panels. Bump ?v=N here.
- css/app.css — all styles.
- js/app.js (~1400 lines) — the whole app: state object S, render loop, tools, panels.
- js/storage.js — IndexedDB wrapper (DB 'mathboard', store 'notebooks', keyPath 'id').
- sw.js — service worker (offline). Bump CACHE on asset changes. Disabled on localhost.
- vendor/ — offline libs (jspdf, pdf.js + worker, mathjs, simple-statistics, uPlot).

ARCHITECTURE:
- Data model: notebook {id,title,pages[]} -> page {id, paper, strokes[], objects[],
  background?, functions?, showResultant, showConjugate}. Persisted debounced 400ms via persist().
- Coordinates: everything stored in PAGE UNITS (PAGE_W=1000 x PAGE_H=1414, A4) so pan/zoom
  never distorts saved work. Camera = {scale, offsetX, offsetY}. UNIT=50 page units = "1" on
  the grid. toPage(cssX,cssY) converts screen->page. snapPt() snaps to integer grid on grid
  papers (argand/vectorgrid/axes) only.
- Strokes: {tool,color,width,points:[{x,y,p}]} with midpoint-quadratic smoothing.
- Objects (page.objects[]), o.kind in vector|line|rect|ellipse|complex|circle|text.
  drawObject() dispatches by kind; objHit() used by eraser + selection.
- Tools (S.tool): pen, highlighter, eraser, lasso (moves STROKES), select (moves/resizes
  OBJECTS via objHandles/applyHandle), line, rect, ellipse, vector, plotz, circle, text.
- Undo: beginAction() snapshots the page; commitAction() pushes to S.undo if it changed.
- Floating panels (draggable): #calc (mathjs), #stats (simple-statistics + uPlot), #graph
  (function grapher). PDF import: PDF.js -> offscreen canvas FILLED WHITE FIRST -> JPEG dataURL.

WORKFLOW (follow on every request):
1. Read the relevant files first. Never edit blind.
2. Give a SHORT plan before writing code.
3. Do ONE solid, self-contained change per round — implement OR fix, then stop.
4. Wrap mutations in beginAction/commitAction. Keep it vanilla and static.
5. Bump ?v=N (index.html x2) and CACHE (sw.js) as the last step.
6. End with: which files changed + what each change does, confirmation you bumped the version,
   and a short step-by-step test checklist for http://localhost:8080 (remind me to hard-refresh
   with Cmd+Shift+R). Verify the change yourself before claiming it works where possible.
